#: ../../B/bag-on-the-side.rst:5
msgid "bag on the side"
msgstr "bag on the side"

#: ../../B/bag-on-the-side.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../B/bag-on-the-side.rst:9
msgid ""
"[prob. originally related to a colostomy bag] An extension to an established"
" hack that is supposed to add some functionality to the original. Usually "
"derogatory, implying that the original was being overextended and should "
"have been thrown away, and the new product is ugly, inelegant, or bloated. "
"Also v. phrase, \"to hang a bag on the side [of]\". \"C++? That's just a bag"
" on the side of C ....\" \"They want me to hang a bag on the side of the "
"accounting system.\""
msgstr ""
"[おそらく元はストーマ袋(人工肛門の袋)に関連]確立されたハックに、元のものに何らかの機能を加えるはずの拡張。たいてい侮蔑的で、元のものが拡張されすぎていて捨てるべきだったこと、そして新しい産物が醜く、洗練されておらず、あるいは肥大していることを含意する。動詞句「[…の]側に袋をぶら下げる(to"
" hang a bag on the side [of])」もある。「C++? "
"あれはCの側に袋をぶら下げただけだ……」「会計システムの側に袋をぶら下げろと言われている」。"
